  <description type="morphology">Stems 10–30 cm, glabrous except densely woolly at base. Leaves: stipules 0.8–3.5 mm; leaf pairs equal; blade 8–25 mm, fleshy. Inflorescences 2–4-flowered. Flowers: perianth 2.2–4.2 mm; hypanthium green, becoming brown and hard, terete to angular; sepals erect to spreading, central portion green, linear to oblong, concave, often unequal, fleshy, scarious portion becoming deciduous with age; staminodes slightly longer than sepals. Utricles ovoid. Seeds 0.9–1.1 mm.</description>
